post_text: Kleptz Drop OFF/Pick Up Procedures
shared_text:
NORTHMONTCITYSCHS.OH.SCHOOLS.BZ
2019/2020 Drop Off/Pick Up Procedures & Times
text:
Kleptz Drop OFF/Pick Up Procedures

NORTHMONTCITYSCHS.OH.SCHOOLS.BZ
2019/2020 Drop Off/Pick Up Procedures & Times

post_text:
If your child is riding the bus, a parent or caregiver needs to be at the bus stop to meet your child at the end of the day. Please be at the bus stop at the regularly scheduled time, even though drop off times might be adjusted due to our kindergarten students learning the process of riding the bus home. If you are not at the bus stop, your child will be returned to the Kleptz Early Learning Center and placed in the YMCA Childcare program. There will be a charge for the Childcare services. The KELC phone number is 832-6750.

If you have any questions regarding transportation, please call the transportation office at 832-5050.
text:

The KELC phone number is 832-6750.

If you have any questions regarding transportation, please call the transportation office at 832-5050.

post_text:
School begins at 9:20 am. Students may arrive at 9:00 am.
Dismissal for car riders is by hallways.
**Car riders in the green and yellow hallways are dismissed at 3:45 pm.
**Car riders in the blue and orange hallways are dismissed at 3:55 pm.
**Families picking up students in the blue and orange hallways please wait at the designated spot by the blue/orange sign until you are given the signal to continue to the pick up location for your child.
**Please remember that if you are parking to walk your child to or from school, you must park in the parking lot. Parking in the drop off/pick up lanes are not permitted.

post_text:
Good evening KELC Families!

We have an issue during student drop-off time in the morning. We need your help. After our staff has entered the building, some families are parking in the drop-off lane to walk their child to the building. This is causing a backup. Other families then try to go around the parked cars and are pulling out in front of families trying to exit the drop-off lane. The left lane is the exit lane in the morning, not a passing lane. Please remember that if you want to walk your child to the door of the building, you need to park in the parking lot and use the crosswalk.

We appreciate everyone taking a little extra time - and slowing down - to make sure we are not creating an unsafe situation for our children and our families.

Thank you for your assistance!

Sincerely,
Dr. Beth Wyandt, Principal
